hould be like.\n\n- Shannon  Mullen, See What Flowers\n|\nWhen the Prince comes into your life, you will stop thinking and start reasoning.\n\n- Jaachynma\n|\ni know it all ends the same, but i was interested in seeing how you would break my heart.\n\n- Ava\n|\nOh, it must be wonderful to be educated. What does it feel like?''It's like having an operation,' said Treece. 'You don't know you've had it until long after it's over.\n\n- Malcolm Bradbury, Eating People is Wrong\n|\nThe entire world is surviving only due to ‘beliefs’, not because of ‘Knowledge’ (Gnan). Every human being is (living) only because of beliefs.\n\n- Dada\n|\nThat pleasure which is at once the most pure, the most elevating and the most intense, is derived, I maintain, from the contemplation of the beautiful.\n\n- Edgar Allan Poe, Poems and Essays\n|\nWe have just enough religion to make us hate, but not enough to make us love.\n\n- David Mitchell, The Thousand Autumns of Jacob de Zoet\n|\nConfidence of a dedicated person, seems to be over-confidence to ordinary masses.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, The Film Testament\n|\nIf you compose your dreams into a music, then your dreams will become the music you will always love to sing.\n\n- Auliq-Ice\n|\nYou should calm down and listen to the voice of your heart. This is your inner voice, your intuition or strong desire or a passion to a certain kind of activity\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWhen you choose to look down on something, you render yourself incapable of understanding it.\n\n- Stewart\n|\nTrue leaders apply law and grace, for those who only apply only law have little influence and those who apply only grace do not influence properly.\n\n- Orrin\n|\nOnly after seeing the winter, do you comprehend the richness of summer. This was a big theme, and one I could confidently do: the infinite variety of nature.\n\n- Martin Gayford, A Bigger Message: Conversations with David Hockney\n|\nJust like a flower, enjoy the joy of giving.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nGood Morning Humans...'